results.description: "Bad attitude".Tasmanian devil. With wildlife photography I like to try to capture the essence of a particular animal species or individual. Tasmanian devils are known for their aggressive habits, and will eat anything they can overcome. According to some scientific research, they have the most powerful bite for their weight of any meat-eating animal, more than hyenas, and easily crunch through bones. I am pleased with this photo because I think it expresses the aggressive, in your face, bad attitude of the species.
